<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>

<head>

<title>SIZE-IS-FUNCTION-OF-AGE</title>

</head>

<body>
	<h3><i>I increase my size with age until I reach full size.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>SIZE-IS-FUNCTION-OF-AGE </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for size-expression minimum (.5 + 0.01 * my-age) 3            
substitute-text-area-for cycle-duration 1          
do-every cycle-duration
   [set size size-expression]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>You can change the initial size (.5 in this example) or the maximum size 

	(3 here). Or the growth rate (0.01 here). Size may be a more complex 

	function of age (or other factors). </p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="GROW-OLDER" href="GROW-OLDER.html">

	GROW-OLDER</a> increases the age of an object. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>After every time unit this sets my size to a function of <i>

	my-age</i> with a maximum value of 3. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>
</body>
</html>
